CrudRepository vs JpaRepository

Both are part of Spring Data JPA and are used to perform database operations.

1️⃣ CrudRepository

Provides basic CRUD operations.

Example:

public interface StudentRepository extends CrudRepository<Student, Integer> {
}
Main Methods
Method	Work
save()	insert / update
findById()	fetch record by id
findAll()	get all records
deleteById()	delete record
count()	count rows
existsById()	check record exists

Return type of findAll():

Iterable<T>
2️⃣ JpaRepository

JpaRepository extends CrudRepository, so it has all CRUD methods + extra features.

Example:

public interface StudentRepository extends JpaRepository<Student, Integer> {
}
Additional Methods
Method	Work
findAll()	returns List
flush()	sync with DB
saveAndFlush()	save and commit immediately
deleteInBatch()	delete multiple records
findAll(Pageable p)	pagination

Return type of findAll():

List<T>
📊 Difference Table
Feature	CrudRepository	JpaRepository
Basic CRUD	✅	✅
Pagination	❌	✅
Batch operations	❌	✅
flush() support	❌	✅
findAll() return type	Iterable	List
Used in projects	Less	Most common
